	<body>
		<!--  ***** GOALS   ************************-->
		<div1 id="goals">
			<head>Goals</head>
			<p>The goal of XML Query 1.1 is to extend XML Query 1.0 with additional functionality in response to requests from users and implementors.</p>
			<p>Satisfying these goals may require changes to the set of seven documents that have progressed to Recommendation together (Data Model, Functions and Operators, Serialization, XPath 2.0, XQuery 1.0, XQueryX, and XSLT 2.0).</p>
		</div1>
		<!--*****REQUIREMENTS**************************************************-->
		<div1 id="Requirements">
			<head>Requirements</head>
			<!-- TERMINOLOGY-->
			<div2 id="terminology">
				<head>Terminology</head>
				<p>The following keywords are used throughout the document to specify the extent to which an item is a requirement for the work of the XML Query Working Group:</p>
				<glist>
					<gitem>
						<label id="terminology-must">MUST</label>
						<def>
							<p>The item is an absolute requirement.</p>
						</def>
					</gitem>
					<gitem>
						<label id="terminology-should">SHOULD</label>
						<def>
							<p>There may exist valid reasons not to treat this item as a requirement, but the full implications should be understood and the case carefully weighed before discarding this item.</p>
						</def>
					</gitem>
					<gitem>
						<label id="terminology-may">MAY</label>
						<def>
							<p>An item deserves attention, but further study is needed to determine whether the item should be treated as a requirement.</p>
						</def>
					</gitem>
				</glist>
				<p>When the words  <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-must" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MUST</loc>, <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-should" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">SHOULD</loc>, or <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-may" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MAY</loc> are used in this technical sense [<loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2119.txt" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">IETF RFC 2119</loc>], they occur as a hyperlink to these definitions. These words will also be used with their conventional English meaning, in which case there is no hyperlink. For instance, the phrase "the full implications should be understood" uses the word "should" in its conventional English sense, and therefore occurs without the hyperlink.</p>


<p id="req-status">Each requirement also includes a status section,
indicating its current situation in the XQuery/XPath/XSLT family of specifications.
Three status levels are used:</p>
<glist>
<gitem>
<label>"Green" status</label>
<def>
<p>
<graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/> This indicates that the requirement, according to its
original formulation, has been completely met. Optional clarifying text
may follow.</p></def></gitem>
<gitem>
<label>"Yellow" status</label>
<def>
<p>
<graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/yellow-ball.gif" alt="yellow status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/> This indicates that the requirement has been partially met
according to its original formulation. When this happens, explanatory text is
provided to better clarify the current scope of the
requirement.</p></def></gitem>
<gitem>
<label>"Red" status</label>
<def>
<p>
<graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/red-ball.gif" alt="red status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/> This indicates that the requirement, according to its
original formulation, has not been met. If this is the case, explanatory text
is provided.</p></def></gitem></glist>

			</div2>
			<!-- GENERAL REQUIREMENTS-->
			<div2 id="general-requirements">
				<head>General Requirements</head>
				<div3 id="backward-compatibility">
					<head>Backward compatibility</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-must" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MUST</loc> be backward compatible. </p>
								<p>Every valid XQuery 1.0 expression <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-must" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MUST</loc> be valid in XQuery 1.1 and it <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-must" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MUST</loc>  evaluate to the same result.</p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="extension-compatibility">
					<head>Extension compatibility</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-must" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MUST</loc> be compatible with XQuery 1.0 extensions developed by the <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="http://www.w3.org/XML/Query/" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">XML Query Working Group</loc>, including <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#UpdateRequirements" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">XQuery Update Facility</loc> and <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#FullTextRequirements" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">XQuery 1.0 and XPath 2.0 Full-Text</loc>.</p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
			</div2>
			<!--  REQUIREMENTS ***********************************-->
			<div2 id="xml-query-functionality">
				<head>XML Query Functionality</head>
				<div3>
					<head>Value-based grouping</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-must" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MUST</loc> include a language facility to specify value-based grouping.</p>


<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="error-processing-and-recovery">
					<head>Error processing and recovery</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-must" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MUST</loc> provide a mechanism to process errors raised by an expression and to return an alternative value. </p>
								<p>This <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-may" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MAY</loc> be implemented by introducing a <emph>try-catch</emph> expression. </p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="numeric-formatting">
					<head>Numeric formatting</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-must" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MUST</loc> include additional library functions or an equivalent mechanism to perform formatting of numeric values.</p>
								<p>It <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-should" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">SHOULD</loc> be similar to the functionality provided in <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#XSLT20" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">XSLT 2.0</loc>, such as by function <code>format-number()</code>.</p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="date-formatting">
					<head>Date formatting</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-must" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MUST</loc> include additional library functions or an equivalent mechanism to perform formatting of date and time values.  </p>
								<p>It <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-should" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">SHOULD</loc> be similar to the functionality provided in <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#XSLT20" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">XSLT 2.0</loc>, such as by functions  <code>format-date()</code>, <code>format-time()</code>, <code>format-dateTime()</code>.</p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="default-values-for-external-variables">
					<head>Default values for external variables</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-must" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MUST</loc> have a mechanism to specify default values for external variables.</p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="non-deterministic-external-functions">
					<head>Non-deterministic external functions</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-must" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MUST</loc> provide a way to denote that an external function is non-deterministic.</p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="positional-grouping">
					<head>Positional grouping</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-should" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">SHOULD</loc> provide a facility for positional grouping of items in a sequence according to specified partitioning conditions. </p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="windowing">
					<head>Windowing</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-should" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">SHOULD</loc> provide a way to iterate over a sequence by several values at a time.</p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="output-numbering">
					<head>Output numbering</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-should" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">SHOULD</loc> provide a mechanism to associate ordinal numbers with the items returned by a FLWOR expression.</p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="dynamic-creation-of-namespace-bindings">
					<head>Dynamic creation of namespace bindings</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-should" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">SHOULD</loc> allow dynamic creation of namespace bindings.</p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="declaration-of-serialization-parameters">
					<head>Declaration of serialization parameters</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-should" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">SHOULD</loc> have a mechanism to specify serialization parameters in the query prolog.</p>
<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="node-references">
					<head>Node references</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-should" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">SHOULD</loc> support creation of a reference to an existing node having the following properties: </p>
								<p>a) the reference could be included in a constructed element </p>
								<p>b) the reference can be dereferenced, returning the original node with the original node id.</p>


							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="outer-for">
					<head>Outer for</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-should" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">SHOULD</loc> provide additional mechanisms to specify joins between sequences.   A possible approach would be to add an "<emph>outer-for</emph>" clause to the FLWOR expression to specify variable binding which is guaranteed to be bound to an empty sequence if there are no other bindings generated.</p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="type-declaration-for-context-item">
					<head>Type declaration for context item</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-should" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">SHOULD</loc> allow explicit type declaration for the context item.</p>
<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="support-for-new-data-types">
					<head>Support for new data types</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-should" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">SHOULD</loc> support new data types introduced in <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#XMLSchema11rec" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">XML Schema 1.1</loc>.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="higher-order-functions">
					<head>Higher order functions</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-may" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MAY</loc> provide an ability to pass a function as an argument to another function and to invoke a function that has been passed as an argument. </p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met. (The proposal is not yet integrated into our internal Working Draft.)</p>

								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-may" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MAY</loc> also provide the ability to define anonymous functions e.g., lambda expressions. </p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met. (The proposal is not yet integrated into our internal Working Draft.)</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="conditional-constructors">
					<head>Conditional constructors</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-may" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MAY</loc> add a language extension to the node constructors to specify, in a compact notation, that a node should be constructed only if its typed value would not be an empty sequence or if it would satisfy some other condition.</p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement is already met by XQuery 1.0, there is no need to introduce new syntax. Either of the following solutions works:</p>
<eg xml:space="preserve">if ($mentor) then attribute mentor { $mentor } else ()</eg>
<eg xml:space="preserve">(attribute mentor { $mentor })[$mentor]</eg>

							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="validation">
					<head>Validation</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-may" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MAY</loc> provide a mechanism to validate an element or document node with respect to a global named type</p>
<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
<p>or against
							  non-global element declarations or types.</p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/red-ball.gif" alt="red status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has not been met.</p>

								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-may" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MAY</loc> provide a mechanism to validate an element or document node against a named schema without importing the schema.</p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/red-ball.gif" alt="red status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has not been met.</p>

							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="type-expressions">
					<head>Type expressions</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-may" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MAY</loc> provide a way to compare the type of an expression to the type of another expression without 
							exposing the type itself.</p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/red-ball.gif" alt="red status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has not been met.</p>

							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="module-composition-restrictions">
					<head>Module composition restrictions</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-may" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MAY</loc> relax the restrictions on the module import feature relating to forward references and circular imports.</p>

<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/green-ball.gif" alt="green status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has been met.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="invocation-of-external-functionality">
					<head>Invocation of external functionality</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-may" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MAY</loc> provide a normative way to invoke external functions and modules that are not implemented in XQuery,  such as functions defined as web services or XSLT functions and templates.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
				<div3 id="static-typing-extensions">
					<head>Static typing extensions</head>
					<glist>
						<gitem>
							<label/>
							<def>
								<p>XQuery 1.1 <loc xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" href="#terminology-may" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="replace" xlink:actuate="onRequest">MAY</loc> extend static typing rules.</p>


<p><graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" source="http://www.w3.org/Icons/red-ball.gif" alt="red status" xlink:type="simple" xlink:show="embed" xlink:actuate="onLoad"/>  
<emph>Status:</emph> this requirement has not been met. Static typing is no longer a normative part of XQuery 1.1.</p>
							</def>
						</gitem>
					</glist>
				</div3>
